Introduction

24K is a five–member boy group under Choeun Entertainment. Originally debuting with seven, They debuted on September 6, 2012 with the mini-album "Hurry Up". The original meaning of their name was "2 dancing machines and 4 main vocals," but through numerous lineup changes it has evolved to mean "like gold, to shine forever."

They rebranded as 24K+ on November 4th, 2023 and redebuted with “Roller Coaster” on the 21st of the same month.
